<br>
She could have, at the very least, taken FMLA time - which is entitled to everyone, regardless of whether or not your state has an &quot;at will&quot; clause.  Don't let them shove her the &quot;30 days notice&quot; line - that's only in forseeable circumstances.  A medical emergency, obviously, isn't classified as such.<br>
